About This Course

Complete the lessons and quizzes in this course for a comprehensive review of what's covered on the Texas Examinations of Educators Standards (TExES) School Counselor exam. Our engaging lessons can help you improve your understanding of student development, different approaches to counseling, and the responsibilities of school counselors. Self-assessment quizzes, chapter exams, and a final exam are provided to ensure you understand the topics covered. Conveniently, 24/7 online access allows you to study at your own pace. You can submit questions to our instructors if you have any questions about the information in the lessons.

Check out our TExES Preparation resources! We've got TExES courses to teach you the material, comprehensive TExES study guides to help you study, TExES practice tests to test your knowledge, and TExES informational articles to get you up to speed on testing logistics.

Syllabus & Course Information

The topics that you should know to do well on the TExES School Counselor exam are covered in this course. You can get an understanding of various counseling theories, strategies for diverse learning environments, and methods for handling crises. Upon completion of this course, you should be able to confidently do the following:

  • Discuss theories of cognitive, social, language, and emotional development
  • Recall stages and processes of physical and motor development
  • Recount factors that can affect human development
  • Describe different theoretical approaches to counseling
  • Discuss roles and responsibilities of school counselors and school counseling programs
  • Explain curriculum development, student assessments, and program evaluations
  • Discuss college, career, individual, and group counseling
  • Name different types of crisis intervention
  • Identify the importance of goal setting and student motivation
  • Outline issues in diversity and equality in school counseling
  • Employ strategies to create diverse learning environments

Course Format

This course contains 18 individual chapters broken down into 201 lessons delivered in text and video formats. You can easily gauge your understanding of the material covered in each lesson by taking self-assessment quizzes and completing each chapter exam.

TExES School Counselor Exam Information

The TExES School Counselor exam is part of the certification process for becoming a school counselor in the state of Texas.

  • Number of Questions: 100 questions
  • Question Type: Multiple-choice
  • Time Limit: 5 hours
  • Exam Cost: $131 (per test)

TExES School Counselor Preparation and Registration

Each chapter of this course is composed of a series of lesson videos that are accompanied by lesson transcripts and quizzes. You can read the lesson transcripts to reinforce your retention of the material presented in the lessons and take quizzes to test your understanding of the lessons. After you've completed all the lessons and quizzes in a chapter, take the practice chapter exam to test your overall understanding of the material before moving to the next.

The TExES School Counseling exam is offered on selected days of year; to check out these dates visit the TExES-ETS website. You will also need to visit this website to register for this exam. Check with your program, or the Texas Education Agency if you are out of state, before you take this exam to get eligibility approval and determine what other TExES tests you may need to take.

TExES School Counselor Scoring

You need a minimum scaled score of 240 in order to pass the exam, and you will find out whether you passed as soon as you complete the test. Score reports are made available within a time period of four weeks following the test date.
